Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language): This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing and semantic parsing, which falls under the scope of cs.CL.
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The use of neural translation models and attention mechanisms in this paper is a common technique in AI research.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The Seq2Seq model used in this paper is a popular machine learning technique for natural language processing tasks.
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The use of neural networks in this paper makes it relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE.
5. cs.SD (Software Engineering): While not the primary focus of the paper, the implementation and testing of the proposed method involves software engineering practices.
